OL,7,FThey often complete the walk tired and
OL,8,Fhungry but spiritually revived. It is
OL,9,Fbelieved that with every step one's
OL,10,Fsins are being erased.
OL,12,FAlong the route, local and
OL,13,Finternational organisations set up
OL,14,Fstations known as mawkibs, laying out
OL,15,Ffree water, food, sweet tea and
OL,16,Fshelter for those who need to rest,
OL,17,Fand Iraqi officials block off hundreds
OL,18,Fof miles of road to ensure the safety
OL,19,Fof those taking part.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
