OL,7,FHe said the pilgrimage has been
OL,8,Fpreviously restricted, especially
OL,9,Funder Saddam Hussein's rule in Iraq
OL,10,Fwhen "the Arbaeen pilgrimage was
OL,11,Fbanned".
OL,13,FDr Nakshawani adds: "Anyone who was
OL,14,Fseen going to Karbala during Saddam
OL,15,FHussain's brutal regime was executed.
OL,16,FIn a personal case, my own uncle.
OL,18,F"So there was that breathing space
OL,19,Fthat emerged in 2003, after the fall
OL,20,Fof the regime. Everyone could finally
OL,21,Fgo back to Karbala".
